I just wanted to say- as a friend of someone with severe anxiety issues (as well as having them myself to a lesser degree)  I want it to be clear that when someone tells you to relax its really not always just an easy go-to phrase to get around giving proper advice. Honestly I often use it as a precursor to a longer discussion, as a sort of "Hey. I'm here." I know some people out there aren't genuine when they say "just relax" or similar things but once in a while people will truly wish to help you. Its true, your mind doesn't work the same as others, and it may be hard for them to understand but there are people out there that want to comfort you and let you know that things really will be okay in the end.
